"""
Created on Mon Jul 26 17:43:46 2021

Given the value of principal, interest and year. You can calculate 
the simple interest using the formula
Sample Interest = (principal * interest * year)/100
Round the value to the nearest integer and print it.

There will be 3 lines of numeric input - 
'a' : principal which is of type float or double.
'b' : interest which is of type integer. 
'c' : year which is again of type integer.

@author: Dhilip.KumarTG
"""

a = float(input())
b = int(input())
c = int(input())
si = abs((a*b*c)/100)
print(int(si))
